HEADWORD: Treatable
<hw>Treat"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>tretable</ets>, F. <ets>traitable</ets>, L. <ets>tractabilis</ets>.
See <er>Treat</er>, and cf. <er>Tractable</er>.]</ety> <def>Manageable;
tractable; hence, moderate; not violent.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
⟦ldquo⟧ A <xex>treatable</xex> disposition, a strong memory.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>R. Parr.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A kind of <qex>treatable</qex> dissolution.</q>
<rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The heats or the colds of seasons are less <qex>treatable</qex>
than with us.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Temple.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Treatably</ent>⟦br⟧
